Whereas African-American males suffer from a prostate cancer incidence rate that is up to
			 65-percent higher than White males and have double the prostate cancer
			 mortality rate of White males;

Whereas screening by a digital rectal examination and a prostate-specific antigen blood test can
			 detect the disease at the early stages, including the chances of survival
			 for more than 5 years to nearly 100 percent;
